# Domain module rules

Business logic lives here — **not** in route handlers, React components, or API route files. This repo uses a flat `src/lib/` (no `src/lib/domain/` subfolder).

## Patterns

1. Validation helpers return `{ ok: true, days } | { ok: false, error }` (see `validateRequestDays` in `src/lib/allowance.ts`) — callers surface `error` to the user, never throw for expected failures.
2. Allowance/day functions accept an optional `db: PrismaClient | Prisma.TransactionClient` parameter so actions can run them inside a `$transaction` — preserve this when adding functions.
3. Authorization checks live in `src/lib/permissions.ts` (`isAdmin`, `isTeamManager`, `canReviewRequest`) — call them before mutating, never inline role logic.
4. Day counting goes through `src/lib/dates.ts` (weekends excluded) and `src/lib/allowance.ts` (public holidays via `holidayCountryCode`); do not reimplement day math.
5. Reuse existing modules — search `src/lib/` before adding new files.

## File naming

Noun-based, one concern per file: `allowance.ts`, `dates.ts`, `permissions.ts`, `public-holidays.ts`, `login-throttle.ts`. Integrations get their own file (`slack.ts`, `notifications/enqueue.ts`).

